)
Inflammation of joints, nearby tissues, and sometimes other organs (
rheumatoid arthritis
)
Inflammation of a joint due to an infection (
septic arthritis
)
Disorder in which the body's immune system attacks healthy tissue (
systemic lupus erythematosus
)
Home Care
For joint swelling after an injury, apply ice packs to reduce pain and swelling. Wrap the ice in a cloth. Do not place ice directly on the skin. Raise the swollen joint so that it is higher than your heart, if possible.
